verbLexeme: 1. Of a person, to move up into the air. English = ascend.
2. Of a person or soul, to go upwards into heaven. English = ascend.
nominalLexeme: 1. Of a person, the act of moving up into the air. English = ascension.
2. Of a person or soul, the act of going up into heaven. English = ascension.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: legs rising into the air.
